\name{association_rules}
\alias{association_rules}
\title{Generate Association Rules}
\description{
Applies the Apriori algorithm to discover associations.
}
\usage{
association_rules(data, support = 0.01, confidence = 0.8)
}
\arguments{
  \item{data}{A transactions object or data that can be coerced into one (e.g., list, matrix, or data frame).}
  \item{support}{Minimum support threshold for the rules (default is 0.01).}
  \item{confidence}{Minimum confidence threshold for the rules (default is 0.8).}
}
\value{
Returns an object of class \code{rules} containing the association rules generated by the Apriori algorithm.
}
\details{
This function converts the input data to a \code{transactions} object and then applies the \code{apriori} function from the \code{arules} package to discover frequent itemsets and association rules based on the given support and confidence thresholds.
}
\examples{
library(arules)
data("Groceries")
rules <- association_rules(Groceries, support = 0.02, confidence = 0.6)
inspect(head(rules))
}
